  "title": "Observations on Pests and Diseases of Wild Cicer Species",
  "abstract": "Preliminary observations of the occurrence of pests and diseases on wild Cicer species in Turkey, Ethiopia and Afghanistan are reported for the first time. Lepidop-teran borers and bruchids appear to be the most serious pests. In most natural habitats, grazing by domestic animals is an important source of damage.",
